Citation.sAbstract: A high-pressure flow-mixing isothermal calorimeter is used to determinate the excess molar enthalpies of five binary systems for methyl acetate and (1-propanol, 2-propanol, 1-butanol, 2-butanol, and 1-pentanol) at T = (298.15 and 308.15) K and p = (5.0 and10.0) MPa. The smooth values calculated by Redlich-Kister equation are also compared with the experimental results.
Citation.sTitle: Excess Molar Enthalpies of Methyl Acetate and (1-Propanol, 2-Propanol, 1-Butanol, 2-Butanol, and 1-Pentanol) at T = (298.15 and 308.15) K and P = (5.0 and 10.0) MPa
